#1. The final executable was compiled on this machine:
no special requirement

#2. How to invoke my program: 
1) ``./rt [lua file]``; without second argument, draw nonhier.lua by default 
2) draw bounding box: change global boolean variable ``drawBx`` in a4.cpp.
3) change MAXLEVEL in algebra.hpp to use mirror recursion.

#3. How to use my extra features: 
I add ``mirror reflection``, by changing MAXLEVEL in algebra.hpp, the maximum recursion depth changes.
reflectin is turned off by default. After changing the parameter, do not forget to call make for recompilation.
screenshot02.png shows the reflectin effect of 2 recursions.
screenshot07.png shows the reflectin effect of 3 recursions.

#4. I have created the following data files, which are in the data directory:
self.lua & pyramid.lua

